itemListElement.name: Coffee Crawl & VIP Morning in Pike Place Market

name: Coffee Crawl & VIP Morning in Pike Place Market
description:
Our guides are not just ordinary tour guides; they are seasoned chefs with extensive culinary expertise, offering a unique perspective. Their background in the industry gives them a profound appreciation for the small businesses we choose to spotlight during our tours. . Our bites are a medley of breakfast treats, and for those who prefer alternatives to coffee, we've got you covered. The concluding hour of our market tours is a truly magical moment, as it marks the awakening of the market for the day, providing an unforgettable experience for our visitors.

Eat Seattle is permitted and licensed by the Pike Place Market PDA to operate tours in the Pike Place Historical District. The PDA requires any business or person conducting tours within it’s properties and in the public areas of the historical district to be pre-approved and to have a license for this activity.

review.name: Coffee crawl pikes place
review.reviewBody: Eric is friendly and knowledgeable and an excellent tour guide!!! Highly recommend. The coffee shops we stopped at were incredible as well.
Our tour guide Eric was awesome, had a great time learning about coffee history in Seattle and some tips for making better coffee at home. The land of origin stop was the best!

review.name: Great time
review.reviewBody: Great time, Eric was very informative and such fun person. Took us to so many cool places and with great snacks along the way.

review.name: Incredible Experience!  A MUST!
review.reviewBody: Eric is very knowledgeable when it comes to coffee and this tour is incredible!  So much knowledge and really get a great education on coffee, something very Seattle!  Highly recommend this tour if you are wanting to attend something “Very Seattle”!

review.name: Great tour
review.reviewBody: Fantastic morning tour of the market. Learned a lot about coffee and really enjoyed some good coffee (and food)! My kids (9 and 12) also enjoyed - the pastries along the way kept them entertained. Was also nice to visit the market before it got crowded!

review.name: One of the BEST ways to experience Pike Place Market!
review.reviewBody: 100/10, this tour was EXCELLENT!! Our pastry chef/tour guide, Scott did an AMAZING job of blending together the history of coffee, the history of Pike Place Market, and the process of making coffee. He even made us some wonderful pour-over! Each shop we visited on the tour had its own unique method of roasting and each cup of coffee its own distinct flavor palette. We even got to sample delicious pastries at each location! This has to be one of the best ways to experience Pike Place Market!

review.name: Great Tour
review.reviewBody: Great tour! Even as locals we really enjoyed it! It was informative and the food and coffee were delicious. The tour guide was fun and relaxed.

review.name: Great for solo travellers!
review.reviewBody: I am so glad I booked on this tour! Chef Eric was our guide and he was excellent. He answered all of our questions and I genuinely learned new things about coffee. The small businesses we visited were lovely and everyone was so welcoming and friendly. We were a fairly small group, so we were able to ask extra questions and learn more about the market. I was travelling to Seattle for business and it was a great activity to squeeze in between work - highly recommend if you are solo travelling, it’s a wonderful experience!

review.name: Amazing Couples Experience
review.reviewBody: Never been on a coffee crawl or any crawl. Our tour was given by Chef Eric. He was very passionate which made  everything an experience. The very last Coffee spot we stopped at was called " Land Of Origin". They gave an Ethiopian coffee experience I will never forget. It was such a cool experience and I would highly recommend.

review.name: AMAZING Tour Guide!!
review.reviewBody: If you are on the fence, book this trip! Eric is SUPER knowledgeable and knows all things coffee, best places to eat, and way more! We walked all around Pike Place Market and stopped at incredible small businesses we would have missed if not with Eric. We went on our first day in Seattle and were able to go back to the spots he suggested after! 100% recommend! Eric is amazing and we were so happy to meet him!

itemListElement.name: Henry Mural Tours - 3 hour Immersive Tour of Seattle

name: Henry Mural Tours - 3 hour Immersive Tour of Seattle
description: Come See The Fun Side of Seattle! The Henry Immersive Experience is a truly unique sightseeing tour. Hop aboard the most colorful tour bus you have ever been on and get ready to explore Seattle through the eyes of artists. As we visit over 20 colorful murals painted by Henry we will learn more about the artist, the development of several of Seattle's most iconic neighborhoods and how art is central to the vibrancy of our city. Our dedicated tour guide will provide an entertaining and slightly educational adventure that will be fun for the whole family. Along the way we will visit the "Hidden Wizard Gallery" to view a collection of Henry's most creative canvas paintings, see two more murals and browse through a selection of Henry merchandise. There will be a couple of stops along the way to grab a tasty beverage, take a break if needed and get up and close with some of Henry's art for that photo that will keep you smiling all year long. We look forward to seeing you soon!

review.name: Fun tour!
review.reviewBody: We loved this tour with Roman.  The murals were beautiful. The stop at the brewery was extra special to be able to stand next to one.

review.name: Best Birthday to share with friends
review.reviewBody: Surprised my bestie with a birthday trip for this tour!  It was FABULOUS .  Roman and Zona were delightful & fun!  I’m a longtime Seattleite, & happily surprised by hidden places I didn’t know existed even in my own neighborhoods. in which I lived.  The day was bright & beautiful & my artist friend said it was the best present she’d ever had (at 62 y. o.).  Highly recommend …. go!!!

review.name: Such a fun adventure!
review.reviewBody: This tour was so much fun!! I went on the tour last fall and decided to bring some friends in March. The tour guide, Roman, is a great narrator and told us so much about the art scene in Seattle and other cities. The murals are all very different -- from decorating a house, fence, retail venue, restaurant, garden and even retaining walls downtown. I think my favorite mural was a walrus riding a bicycle. The bus is very comfortable and full of Henry's art. Look for the giraffe that is hiding behind the driver.  I purchased a picture and mementoes at Henry's gallery. I'll definitely take the tour again.

review.name: Amazing tour of Henry’s art
review.reviewBody: This was absolutely the most fun I have ever had on a sight seeing tour! Fun bus, knowledgeable tour guide and so much amazing art. If you are thinking about taking this tour, trust me, go. So. Much. Fun!

review.name: A look of Seattle’s art world!
review.reviewBody: The tour was filled with beautiful murals and fun little tidbits of Seattle history. Ryan Henry Ward, the artist, even made a surprise visit on the tour!

review.name: Great experience with visiting parents!
review.reviewBody: Took my parents on this tour to show them the quirky side of Seattle. Tour guide and driver were incredibly friendly and the entire tour was very engaging. Very fun way and unique way to learn about the history of murals in general in Seattle and see the neighborhoods from a different perspective. My dad is disabled and the driver was very considerate when pulling over for stops. The stops were well timed at a brewery and at a quick drink/food spot. I’ve recommended this experience to my friends as a great activity with visiting parents.

review.name: Henry Mural Tour experience
review.reviewBody: The Henry tour was awesome! Our guide, Roman, was so cool, and you can tell he is passionate about the art. We visited dozens of the artist's murals throughout the city, as well as his gallery/gift shop. His caricatures are sure to bring a smile to your face and he makes Sasquatch look like someone you'd love to meet. And you can visit some primo watering holes to wet your lips and fill your belly. If you are in Seattle, and have a few hours, you can't go wrong with this tour.

review.name: Wonderful tour
review.reviewBody: Our group of 5 had a great time.  The tour guide, David, was very informative and funny.  He did a great job of explaining the reason for the characters in each mural and also explained the history of the Seattle neighborhoods.  There were two pleasant surprises not mentioned in the tour description.  #1:  Tour stops at Ruebens Brewery  to sample beer, use the bathroom, and look at a fabulous mural inside.  #2:  We stopped at Flatstick Pub to look at more Henry art and eat lunch. We didn’t expect a lunch stop,  Our tour ended at 3 pm instead of 2 pm.  Which was no problem for our group.  But if you take this tour, I recommend not having an appointment immediately after 2 pm.

review.name: More than a mural tour!!
review.reviewBody:
David, the tour guide was absolutely amazing and so knowledgeable of Seattle history. The tour is fabulous because it points out not only Henry’s murals but other murals. I was shocked after living in Seattle since 1981 how many murals I had missed in my own city!  The tour is so much more than simply driving by murals. David’s enthusiasm for the art, and art history of Seattle is so contagious.  
A great trip for Seattleites and visitors!!!

review.name: Very interesting!
review.reviewBody: I loved seeing so many of the Henry murals in one go! They are full of life and have a whimsical, uplifting feeling about them. David Roman was a perfect fit as the tour guide, and his knowledge and enthusiasm for Henry's work was obvious. It was a joy to go on this tour, and I would definitely  recommend it!

itemListElement.name: Private Tour of Snoqualmie Falls and Woodinville Wine Tasting

name: Private Tour of Snoqualmie Falls and Woodinville Wine Tasting
description: This tour offers a unique and diverse experience that showcases some of the most iconic locations in WA state with our signature touch of luxury. We pair memorable experiences with memorable service, attention to detail, and depth of knowledge. This is especially true as our groups dive into the history and local significance of the beautiful Snoqualmie Falls during this tour. After we've taken in the grandeur of the falls we will partake in some delectable bites and wine tastings at some of our favorite off-the-beaten-path tasting rooms in Woodinville. If your group wishes we have the ability to elevate this experience even further with the optional inclusions of an unbelievable brunch at the Salish Lodge, unique bottle-blending experiences in Woodinville, and even the ability to start or end your day with a flightseeing tour via plane, helicopter, or hot air balloon!

address.streetAddress: 11805 Renton Ave S, Suite C, Seattle, WA 98178
1410 NE Campus Pkwy University of Washington

itemListElement.name: Winter Day Tour to Longmire on Mount Rainier from Seattle

name: Winter Day Tour to Longmire on Mount Rainier from Seattle
description:
One of the best times of year to visit Mount Rainier is in the winter months. When the days get shorter, the summer crowds head home, and the park turns into a true winter wonderland, come visit Longmire in Mount Rainier National Park!

Stroll through the old-growth forests, where Douglas fir, hemlock, and cedar trees dwarf visitors. The bubbling natural springs tell a story of what lies beneath this abundant and volatile landscape. Experience the natural silence that takes hold as the snow dusted trees insulate the world around you. Learn the diverse history the Longmire area and how this region has attracted visitors long before it was a national park.

After arriving at Mt. Rainier, you will get out to experience as much of the Longmire area as possible for the day. Explore beyond the vehicle during walks and hikes with your guide by your side the entire time. If conditions call for snowshoes, your guide will provide an introductory lesson on how to stay safe and enjoy your walk.

review.name: Excellent day trip with Evergreen Escapes
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful day visiting Longmire and Mount Rainier in winter. Lucky to get a crystal clear day giving us fabulous views of Mount Rainier from various locations throughout to park. Our guide (Brent Maphis) was great fun and shared his excellent knowledge of nature with the group. Everything went smoothly on the day, van was in good condition and plenty of food and snacks provided.

review.name: Nice Day Trip to a beautiful Park
review.reviewBody:
This was my second trip through Evergreen Escapes.    

Easy pickup from downtown hotel, and only 7 people on the trip, so lots of room in the van.   

It was Mid November and we had a crystal clear and cool day.   The temperature was say 40 degrees when we arrived at an overlook to the park and got a list of the itinerary for the day.    

First stop after pictures at the entrance to the park was at Longmire parking lot.   Here we went on a short hike along the Trail of the Shadows.   It is about .7 mile and has some interesting thermal features that reminds you that there is a volcano underneath your feet .    This was a very fit group and even with the guide explanations of everything we completed this in about 15 minutes.

I was pushing for a longer hike ( maybe to carter falls) but I don't think that the guide was allowed to take us any farther into the park.   But she did start us up the Wonderland trail where we put in a 5+ mile out and back hike along a river.  A strenuous couple of minutes before the trail leveled out and the rest of the hike was quite enjoyable.   The guide headed everyone back to the Longmire parking area where she heated up some soup and lunch.   

Post lunch we hiked the Twin Firs loop which is a do not miss hike when on that side of the park.  Lots of huge 500 year old trees were a pleasure to walk through.    

Then a 2 hour drive back to Seattle for a drop off at  our hotel.    

Very nice day hike.   I would recommend the tour to anyone who likes to hike and is in downtown Seattle.

review.name: fulfilling day
review.reviewBody: Admiring Mount Rainier from Seattle is great but getting to go into the park and learn about the history, local ecosystems, and wildlife was a really fulfilling experience. My guide, Mal, had a warm, personable demeanour and seemed to know everything about the Longmire area, making the tour both enjoyable and informative. Super fun day, I'm glad I went.

itemListElement.name: Happy Hour Tour of Pike Place Market

name: Happy Hour Tour of Pike Place Market
description:
Tasty Tours invites you out for cocktails and a deep dive into the nightlife of Seattle's iconic Pike Place Market. Embark on an unforgettable Happy Hour adventure with Supersonic John - The only Market Family tour guide.

You will learn the history, culture and stories that make the Market so special. Purchase whatever cocktail, wine, beer or libation you enjoy along the way as we navigate the 9 acre maze that is the Pike Place Market historic district after dark, Meet Market locals while discovering the speakeasies, hidden gems and out of the way special spots that only a local can show. Beginning with complimentary appetizers at the Athenian - filming location of the hit film "Sleepless in Seattle" and ending at the White Horse home of the strongest drink in Seattle. You will definitely have a great time. Included is a 10% discount at many of the vendors on the Tasty Tours food tour for returning shoppers.

Come do Happy Hour with Supersonic John and drink like a local!

review.name: It was amazing . I got to try a variety of different foods and desserts. I meet a lot of different talented people
review.reviewBody: Chef John was the best tour guide you could ever ask for ! He’s very knowledgeable and got me amazing discounts ! Please hurry and book your tour !

review.name: High Recommend Chef John!
review.reviewBody: Chef John is very knowledge, definitely recommend his tours! We are Seattle locals and learned so much about the market. Great insider information and a fun time all around. The Pimms Cup is something else - not for the faint of heart!

review.name: Awesome Happy Hour Hidden Tour
review.reviewBody: Awesome tour with John! As a local, I’ve been around Pike Place quite a bit, but John showed me many places I didn’t know and helped us meet market artists, fishermen, and restaurant owners. It’s great to see the market when it’s after dark and quiet and still know that there’s a lot of life there! It’s a BYOB (buy your own booze tour) but we did get a free drink and some free food as well, plus happy hour prices made for some affordable drinks! Would 100% recommend, even to locals.

review.name: Made us feel a part of the pike market family
review.reviewBody: Top notch tour I would recommend to friends and family. John is part of the pike market family and made us feel as if we were part of that family as well. Amazing night where we had some great drinks, saw awesome one of a kind bars and met some great people. I’ll go again next time we come to Seattle. Thanks John for a great experience.

itemListElement.name: Outdoor Escape Room in Seattle - Seattle Center

name: Outdoor Escape Room in Seattle - Seattle Center
description:
An immersive clue-solving adventure around Seattle Center. Search for real-world clues, solve puzzles, and discover the neighborhood with an experience you'll never forget!

Reschedule anytime with no fees.

It's a scavenger hunt, escape room, and urban crawl all-in-one. Follow the storyline around town as you find clues and use them to crack codes. Then enter solutions on the app to find out where to go next. Clues can be anywhere - murals, statues, landmarks, and more!

Plan on about two hours of playtime, depending on your experience level and how much time you spend exploring along the way. Difficulty level is adjustable - take as many or as few hints as you’d like!

Bookings made a week or more in advance receive their kit in the mail. Bookings made less than a week in advance will pick up their kit at the start point on the day of the adventure - exact pickup location is sent after booking.

review.name: Best of all worlds!
review.reviewBody:
Really fun time solving the puzzle with friends! I loved the way that local public art factored into the puzzle, and appreciate the work done to weave it into the story! We also noticed details we hadn't seen before. I'm interested in trying one in another city sometime!
Tip - Take a notepad with you so you have a scratch pad for notes and ideas.

review.name: A new fun way to enjoy the city!
review.reviewBody:
We started off pretty slow, but people eventually got into it. We had the most fun working together to get it solved instead of trying to make it competitive. 

There were many things in our experience that made us laugh and we continue to reference. I would recommend this adventure to any group of friends that want to add a little extra fun to a city hangout. Be ready for a challenge and use all your resources. After the last challenge you might be wanting more!

review.name: Great for Families
review.reviewBody: Two moms took four children, ranging in age from 9 to 11. The kids all loved it and it was a great way to get them out of the house! There was brain activity in solving the puzzles (they had to use most of the "hints" but could solve with some prodding), physically activity in running from one real world hint to the next, and social emtional learning in trying to give everyone turns to solve the puzzles with out spoiling it! I highly recommend for anyone looking for something fun to do with their kids!

review.name: Great Escape Room x Scavenger Hunt
review.reviewBody: Fun puzzles set around Seattle Center. Hint system is nice. We started at the armory and it was difficult to watch the videos there, but the transcripts were useful. The adhesive on the envelops can be tough, so maybe have something that can open letters handy.

review.name: Fun for both beginners and long time puzzle enthusiasts!
review.reviewBody: I did this with a group of 4 friends and it took us just under 1.5 hours. We have a lot of escape room and puzzle game experience so we found it to be pretty easy, but in a satisfying way, with fun puzzles that incorporated local art in creative ways. It would be fun to see more versions for different neighborhoods and with varying difficulty!

review.name: Exceeded our expectations by far! A total MUST
review.reviewBody: This experience was amazing and so much fun! Easy to follow directions, high quality contents and surprisingly new things to discover even for locals! Highly recommended! Can't wait for the next one!

review.name: Highly Recommend Fun
review.reviewBody: We had such a good time! We played with our 10-year-old. The difficulty was good and once we got the hang of it we had a blast. Thank you so much for the fun family day!

review.name: So fun
review.reviewBody: Oh my goodness, we loved this! We don’t live in Seattle, but I thought it would be fun to get it and bring with us on our trip. I was worried we would need to know more about where we were, but that wasn’t an issue at all! We loved walking around the area and discovering things we would’ve just walked past, the clues were challenging and fun, and we saved them to bring home to show our friends and family! We hope to do one of them again one day! Being in southeastern Idaho, we really hope for ones for Boise and Salt Lake City!!

review.name: New City, New Details to See!
review.reviewBody:
We met up with a couple friends that lived in the area. Everyone enjoyed the box and the puzzles were things a 10 year old child was enjoying helping with. As someone who never really stopped to look at everything near the area before, this was a great way to do so. 

We went during a time where one of the puzzles relied on a location closed off due to construction. Thanks to the wonderful hints, we were able to get through it. Overall a wonderful time through Seattle and loved that they incorporated a local business into the puzzle.

name: Bungee Workout Class
description:
We are the exclusive fitness studio that teaches Bungee Workout on the west coast. You'll get to experience a fun and invigorating workout that will challenge your coordination, cardio endurance and core strength. It's even more awesome to try it with family and friends, and take home with you photos and videos of you flying on the bungee!

We're just a short walk from the Seattle Center and Key Arena, so add us to your Seattle itinerary, and spice up your vacation with Bungee Workout!

itemListElement.name: Seattle MTB Tour: Beginner to Intermediate

name: Seattle MTB Tour: Beginner to Intermediate
description: Beginner to intermediate days are designated for new or casual adventurers. This is a great option for anyone who is curious about mountain biking or interested in learning basic mountain biking skills. This Seattle tour option would also work great for a ride with a group of friends with a variety of skill levels.

review.name: Exciting experience
review.reviewBody: It was my first mountain biking experience and the tour guide was very nice and he taught me step by step mountain biking. I had only tried manual biking before and fat tire mountain bikes are so different with suspension system but really fun once we know how to balance on them. Thank you for wonderful experiences!

review.name: What an amazing family experience!!!
review.reviewBody:
We are new to the mountain biking world and had the most amazing time with Matt and his crew. We are an active outdoor family but never had tried true mountain biking before and was super excited to learn this activity so we can continue to ride safely.  My boys are 12 & 11 and do a lot of city trail riding and did awesome! We spent the day learning the trails at Duthie Hill Mountain Bike Park and can't wait to do it again!  We learned how to maneuver our bikes safely along the trails, learned trail etiquette as well as learned the benefits of having a good quality bike while riding on a mountain trail.

We were also provided lunch during our day tour which was delicious! I loved that we spent the entire day out doors together as a family and everything was provided for us on this tour, from water, safety gear, bikes, food and snacks as well as transportation straight from our front door!!! Amazing!!!
My boys could not stop talking about this experience and can't wait to do this again!! 

If your looking for a fun activity this summer, I would not hesitate to get this on your calendar!!

review.name: Fantastic Bike Excursion
review.reviewBody: Absolutely amazing trip!!! My wife has not ridden much and Matt helped her ride with confidence. Guides are knowledgable about the trail system and encouraging at every skill level! We HIGHLY recommend this trip!

review.name: Great mountain bike beginner tour
review.reviewBody: Great and knowledgeable tour guide Ben, very easily guided us through beginner training and great early trails, up into some intermediate trails, exhilarating downhills and time for, and alternatives for various rider skill levels made it very enjoyable and worth the time! Will definitely go back for higher skill levels!

review.name: Super fun day!
review.reviewBody: This was my first time mountain biking and I loved the experience. We had great support and instruction from the team. We got to experience a range of trails and the equipment we were given was really good. I can't wait to get back on a mountain bike again!

review.name: Fun day with great instruction
review.reviewBody: Noone else signed up for my tour, but instead of cancelling like many companies would do, I ended up getting a private tour. It was my first time mountain biking and Ben was very helpful with instruction and tips. We spent the morning in the bike park getting comfortable with riding and having some fun. After a good lunch at a local restaurant, we rode up and down a mountain trail a couple times. It was a great workout, fun when I would finally relax going downhill, and I came away feeling much more confident in my biking skills.

review.name: Amazing time!
review.reviewBody:
My S.O. and I did this tour with Erik Barton as our guide. It was so much fun! I had never been mountain biking before and it had been 10+ years since my partner had done it. The bikes used were fantastic and Erik provided everything from gear to water to lunch. Pick-up and drop off was right at our hotel, which was very convenient. 

My partner and I both felt challenged and very accomplished by the end of the day. I was very cautious on some of the downhill areas, but never felt pressured to go faster than I was comfortable with. (I even walked some sections to make sure I avoided injuring myself.)  We had the best experience, and now I'm really excited to try mountain biking again! I'd highly recommend this tour and Erik Barton.

review.name: Eric and Robbie went above and beyond.
review.reviewBody: My wife and I went on our 10 year anniversary and bike riding was a big deal for her. There was high expectations on this trip and our two guides Eric and Robbie really brought the meats. They both went above and beyond with great dialogue, humor, and honestly made me a much better rider after this trip was done with huge amounts of requested advice and encouragement. You will want to request these guys. What a blast.

review.name: Incredible Day
review.reviewBody: What an incredible day on the trails. Our family with four boys ages 15-10 had a memorable day mountain biking with guides Matt and Miles. The guides made it fun for everyone. They assessed our skills and chose great trails. They combined style lessons and pointers with challenging us to push past our comfort zones and improve. I felt very safe and confident in the hands of Miles and Matt and we all enjoyed the day. Our teenagers have thanked us over and over for arranging the day of mountain biking. I highly recommend Seattle Mountain Biking tours.

review.name: Had Miles of fun on the trail!!
review.reviewBody: My husband and I wanted to experience the local scene on our vacation to Seattle and found this mountain bike tour. With no experience whatsoever we learned the fundamentals and were on the trails in no time. Miles was our guide and he was excellent!! We had a blast going through the trails and learning some new techniques. Mountain bikes are already on the Christmas wish list!

name: Seattle Vice Tour
description: Visit a Cannabis grower, processor & retail establishment, Whiskey Distillery and Wine Tasting Room.

address.streetAddress: 2520 Westlake Ave N on Lake Union, directly beneath the AGC building

itemListElement.name: Smith Tower Straight Up Observatory Access Ticket

name: Smith Tower Straight Up Observatory Access Ticket
description:
Smith Tower is improving our guest experience and is undergoing renovations to our museum and box office. All ticket types are now just one price! We look forward to seeing you soon!

Enjoy Smith Tower like you've never seen it before. Immerse yourself in new exhibits that take you on a journey through the past one hundred and ten years. Make your way to the top of the tower for an amazing vantage point from the Observatory, including an open-air deck with 360-degree views of Seattle and beyond. Then take a moment to indulge in Prohibition-era inspired craft cocktails and shareable plates with a group of friends or your loved ones. And don't forget to make a wish in the Wishing Chair. It's the perfect selfie to post of your visit to Smith Tower.

review.name: A must see
review.reviewBody: A great location and view, staff were friendly and the drinks were amazing. Building is beautiful and clean, we had a great couple of hours

review.name: Skyline Sips & Stunning Views!
review.reviewBody:
Our visit to the Smith Tower Observatory was an absolute treat! From the moment we stepped into the historic elevators, there was a buzz of excitement as we climbed to the top of one of Seattle’s most iconic landmarks. Once at the observatory, we were greeted by breathtaking, unobstructed views of the city skyline from the sparkling waters of Puget Sound to the towering silhouette of Mount Rainier in the distance.

The atmosphere is casual yet charming, with vintage decor that nods to the tower’s rich history. We made the most of it by grabbing a couple of drinks and some light bites from the bar both were pleasantly good and paired perfectly with the view. The cocktails especially felt like a little luxury as we sipped them with the city sprawling below us.

It’s not just a pretty view either; the informational displays around the observatory offer fun historical tidbits about Seattle and the tower itself, adding depth to the experience. We ended up lingering longer than planned, soaking in the sunshine and city sounds from above.

Only small note: it can get a little crowded at peak times, so plan ahead if you want a quieter experience. But overall, a fantastic way to see Seattle from a new perspective!

review.name: Richard guided tour
review.reviewBody: Richard was a great and entertaining tour guide. I would definitely suggest taking the guided tour, such amazing history.

review.name: Nice elevator ride.
review.reviewBody: The building is really cool. The museum area is small.  The views from the observation deck are awesome.  No ambiance in bar and drinks were ok.

review.name: The ticket is for the elevator-don't expect to have a drink in the bar
review.reviewBody: Extremely dissatisfied and disappointing.  We purchased 8 tickets for an after work event.  When we arrived, they said we could take the elevator up but that the bar was full, and it didn't matter that we had tickets for our time slot.  The employees were dismissive and stated that website clearly said the $15 was for the elevator.

review.name: Top of Seattle
review.reviewBody:
I went in March 2024.

Decide to visit the oldest tallest building in Western States.

Upon arrival, I was little bit confused with the entrance. Found the ticket. I had pre purchased drink as well. 

Soon I was navigated  the hall to elevator. Prior to elevator, there was bit of museum/history shown about how Smith Tower operated.

When getting on the elevator, the gentleman narrated story about the building. His knowledge is superior!

Finally up at the top of the building, I first decided to get something to drink and sat by the window. You can see the Puget Sound, Bainbridge Island and West Seattle of course the stadiums. Nice view. I decided to step outside to view. The weather at the time was cool. Not that cold. Just Seattle weather. I took couple of photos. I don’t remember if I did see Space needle.

The whole experience is phenomenal. I love it!

Highly recommend!

review.name: Drinks with the ultimate Seattle view
review.reviewBody: A gorgeous location to enjoy cocktails and a 360-view.  The preservation of Seattle history while offering a unique menu was done well here.  I enjoyed catching up with friends, and the photo feature was fun, too.

review.name: You won't regret it
review.reviewBody: Take the Talking Tour. You get a lot of information about the past. Fascinating and well worth it. The views are excellent. I highly recommend the tour.

review.name: Historical Master piece
review.reviewBody: Go go go take the talking tour with Richard so worth it. History with this building is sensational.. have a cocktail and enjoy the view at the top⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

review.name: Great views and fun interactive exhibit.
review.reviewBody: The Smith Tower building is fantastic. Fun to ride up in the classic elevator. The interactive exhibit was quite inventive and fun. You can plug into the old switchboard and overhear conversations that would have taken place. You can type on the antique typewriter. And you learn all about the history before going up. I loved the 360 degree view of the city from the Observation deck. Especially fun after doing the underground tour earlier in the day.

name: 2 Hour Sound Tour
description:
Puget Sound was created when the area's glaciers began their retreat about 14,000 years ago, leaving behind intricate patterns of islands, inlets, lakes and shorelines.

Enjoy the rich ecosystem of Puget Sound on this two hour kayaking tour. This is a great chance to see seals, sea lions, great herons and more. The route of the tour will vary based on recent sightings of local wildlife. Whether you want to drift among the bull kelp or paddle hard along the shore, this tour is for you. 

Meet at our docks in Shilshole Marina 20 minutes prior to tour departure

Family Friendly

Beginner paddlers welcome

What to bring:
Warm clothes, preferably non-cotton
Water-appropriate shoes
A water-proof, wind-proof layer
Water bottle
Sunglasses and/or a sun hat

Please note that if your booking is for an odd number of people, the odd person might be paired up with a new friend or guide in a tandem kayak.

review.name: Puget Sound Adventure
review.reviewBody: Wonderful trip on Puget Sound!  Our guide was kind, helpful, informative with lots of local history and wildlife facts.  Don’t miss this opportunity!

review.name: So FUN! Totally nerded out
review.reviewBody: Booked the Ballard Locks Tour for myself and two civil engineer friends who were visiting from out of town. We all LOVED the tour. We saw wildlife and learned about the sound and infrastructure of the area. We were able to enter the lock twice. It was very, very cool. Lindsay was an excellent guide and very knowledgeable. I would totally recommend this!

review.name: Relaxing, informative, and great sights!
review.reviewBody: Relaxing, informative, and great sights!  This was a tour of the Sound, and it was so enjoyable.  The guide shared great information about the Sound, the area, and especially the bridges.  He took us under the bridge, told stories, and really gave such a great overall understanding of the Sound and the area.  Our favorite part was seeing the seals!

review.name: Exceptional, personable, knowledgeable service
review.reviewBody: Everything about our kayaking experience was stellar. We arrived a bit early and our kayaks were all set to go. We were told where to find the public restrooms - which was helpful seeing as we were headed out after lunch for two hours. Cat was our tour guide and she was exceptional. She went through the instructions thoroughly but concisely and we were out on the water right away. We happened to be the only two kayaks heading out (other reservations were moved that day to other time slots per the requests of those kayakers).  It was a gorgeous day and Cat gave us tons of interesting facts about the area. She also kept us going at an appropriate pace. We really enjoyed our outing in the Puget Sound. Very highly recommend doing it!!

review.name: Great kayak in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Amazing kayak on puget sound.  Harbor seals, baby seals and birds for wildlife.  It was a quiet day so an easy paddle.  Cat was a terrific guide.  Highly recommend!

review.name: The best way to spend a couple hours in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Inspiring and simultaneously relaxing. Amazing views, saw lots of wonderful creatures, and learned a lot about Seattle's geology and geography. Lindsay was an wonderful and highly informative guide. Totally recommend!

review.name: Incredible experience packed with fun and adventure with the best guides!
review.reviewBody: We took the 2 hour Sound tour.  This was only our second time kayaking:  my husband and I felt right in our element.   The entire group was so much fun!  Our guides: Lindsay and Cat were the absolute best!!     They made the entire experience so amazing and surpassed any expectation we had.  This event was packed with fun and so incredibly enjoyable.  Thanks to Lindsay and Cat for making this the best experience ever!! And….the seals….oh my!!  I was in heaven!!

review.name: Sea Lions everywhere!
review.reviewBody: What a treat!  We kayaked amongst sea lions, seal pups, and starfish were showing near the pilings (by the business).  Lindsay was a friendly, kind, and helpful tour leader.   I have already recommended this fantastic trip to others.   All abilities will have a great time!

review.name: Great fun
review.reviewBody: Great time and gorgeous views of the sound and some cool animals!  Blaine was an awesome guide. Definitely recommend!

review.name: Great Experience Kayaking through the Locks
review.reviewBody: We had a great time! We did the Locks Tour and despite being locals, learned a ton about the area, tides, marine life, etc. The guides were helpful, funny, friendly, and knowledgeable. Highly recommend for visitors to the region as we saw seals, Heron, Osprey, etc. Also recommend for locals who want to go through the locks in a small craft!

itemListElement.name: Seattle Seahawks Football Game Ticket at Lumen Field

name: Seattle Seahawks Football Game Ticket at Lumen Field
description:
Seeing the Seattle Seahawks live at Lumen Field is an unforgettable experience that stands out in the NFL for several compelling reasons. With a passionate fanbase, a home-field advantage unlike any other, and a historic franchise, attending a Seahawks game in this stadium will offer you one of the most exciting and dynamic NFL experiences.

Lumen Field is famously known as one of the loudest stadiums in the NFL. The 12th Man, as Seahawks fans are known, create an electric atmosphere that is unparalleled in the league. The Seahawks always match that energy with their play on the field. Famous for their “Legion of Boom” defence in the early 2010’s that saw them win a Super Bowl in 2013, the Seahawks have produced some of the most iconic teams in recent NFL history.

If you want to experience high-energy football, iconic rivalries, and an unforgettable atmosphere, attending a Seattle Seahawks game at Lumen Field is a must. Become part of the 12th Man in this NFL experience of a lifetime!

name: Seattle Houseboat & Neighborhood Walking Tour
description:
Explore Seattle’s quirkiest neighborhood with an expert guide sharing commentary on the culture of the Fremont neighborhood of Seattle.
You’ll have a rare opportunity to climb aboard a Lake Union houseboat (similar to“Sleepless in Seattle”) to learn what it’s like to live on the water (literally) from one of its inhabitants. Exclusive access – only available on this tour!
Wander the Fremont neighborhood, hub of Seattle’s public art scene and counterculture, with your informative and entertaining guide, who will be sure to introduce you to the famous Troll under the bridge, Vladamir Lenin & more!
This tour begins in downtown Seattle and includes a ride on a city transit bus (fare included) with your guide navigating the way. The tour wraps up in Fremont at noon, where you’ll have the opportunity to continue exploring the neighborhood on your own (grab lunch or settle in at a local brewery for a tasting) or ride the bus back into downtown Seattle with your guide – the choice is yours!

review.name: 100% Recommend!
review.reviewBody:
Took this tour on an early Sunday morning, and Daniel was THE BEST 🙂
Started at the troll, which was fun to see in person. And there weren't a lot of people there, so we got great pics.
Being able to go on an actual houseboat was so cool!
And the chocolate was delicious.
Throughout the entire tour, Daniel was personable, social, and friendly. He's very knowledgeable about Seattle sites and history, which was much appreciated!
We stayed in Belltown and would not have made our way to Fremont on our own, so I was very happy to have found this tour online. 
This tour was worth the money while visiting Seattle!!!

With over 10 years of experience in Seattle, we’ve built a strong reputation for delivering reliable, first-class service to both local and international clients. Whether you’re traveling for business or leisure, let us provide you with a smooth, worry-free ride, making your airport transfer the easiest part of your trip.

itemListElement.name: Mad Scientist Drink Fusion Lab, A Mocktail Focused Workshop

name: Mad Scientist Drink Fusion Lab, A Mocktail Focused Workshop
description:
Labora​tory: A place providing an opportunity for experimentation, observation, or practice in a field of study.

This is an ever-changing and high-concept mocktail workshop (aka. laboratory) for those with 0 to 100 levels of experience. Unconventional, not a class; learn through experimentation! You get to take risks in this lab with hundreds of ingredients at your fingertips that you wouldn't normally take at home or in a cocktail class. Tools include smoking guns, test tubes, shaker sets, etc.

It is my goal as your host to work with each of you and fine-tune each event to fit your individual mixology goals. By design, any awkwardness and negative judgment is kicked out the door in order for the madness to ensue!

review.name: BEWARE OF SCAM
review.reviewBody: Would not recommend. The lab was sticky and unclean with leftovers from the night before. The utensils had old food stuck to them, and the snacks were stale or expired. The instructor came in and said she would clean and restock, but she never did. The gingerale and drinks were flat, and the glassware for instagram pictures was dirty. We weren't aware that there was ice until she told us halfway in through the class... for $100 per person, it was a sorry experience.

review.name: Mocktail workshop
review.reviewBody: I think the beauty of the Mad scientist drink Fusion Lab was that it was focused on Mocktails and that it was fun and authentic.  Everyone was themselves, and you are allowed to have fun making Mocktails and learning from everyone in the room and it is perfectly okay to make a mistake!  Matter of fact, you are encouraged to go outside your comfort zone and show that element of creativity. Jen and her team were great at hosting us and the ambience was very warm and welcoming.  The space and venue/loft had a close and intimate feeling as well as being right in the heart of Seattle.  Def. a must do if you are looking to meet new people or just trying something with your partner/friends or just doing something fun in Seattle!

review.name: Amazing Experience!
review.reviewBody: This is an amazing experience.  This is the most unique and fun way to experiment with cocktail and mocktail ingredients you wouldn't otherwise have access to! It's not a class but Jen has wealth of knowledge on cocktail techniques and will help you with whatever drink creation you can imagine!

review.name: Soild, Great, and Fun Experience
review.reviewBody:
Fantastic selection of mixers! Good selection of non-alcoholic spirits. Had a good high-level crash course and she was super helpful, personable, and knowledgeable. And fun props!

I would definitely recommend this for anyone looking to expand on their knowledge of mocktails. The lessons are applicable to cocktails as well!

review.name: Amazing
review.reviewBody:
My friend found out about this experience and asked me to go because I love mocktails. I thought this would be a mocktail class but it was actually a free for all drink making experimentation lab, no lessons on technique, but still a great experience. I had a lot of fun.

We first donned lab coats and chose our mad scientist names. Jen, the owner, gave us a 10 minute introduction of all the stations and we were let loose in the lab to concoct our own drink creations.

The experience was rather immersive in an atelier-like workspace that is decorated with old books and antique trinkets. It felt like I was in an eclectic mad scientist’s lab/apothecary type of environment. There were vials, funnels, shakers, stirrers, measuring spoons, tweezers—all manner of lab tools to aid in experimentation.

The best part about this lab is the variety of ingredients I got to discover and sample. There were ingredients I didn’t even know about or wouldn’t even think to buy myself. I enjoyed trying the freeze dried juice powders, various bitters, the non-alcoholic liquors, and edible glitter.

There were nice touches like a smoker to smoke your drink with wood chips, herb plants to pick fresh herbs, fun dehydrated fruit pieces for garnish, and fresh citrus. There was also an infusion station with various spices, dried herbs, and teas. Jen made sure to supply everything you would need to create the ultimate drink! I felt like a kid in a candy store.

There were also bulk bin snacks provided like wasabi peas, walnuts, gummies, chocolates covered almonds, and banana chips along with charcuterie from the deli in the Melrose Market.

Lastly there were 8 participants in this lab and I felt that was just the right amount of people. I didn’t feel crowded or like I was competing for tools/space. We had free roam in the lab and Jen was very generous with sharing some of the more exotic and expensive ingredients. I like how I didn’t feel restricted or limited in resources or time. The 2 hour time allotted felt enough.

I definitely recommend this experience and I would for sure go back!

review.name: Mocktail lab
review.reviewBody:
We visited today, and this was a fun way to spend a Sunday afternoon.   

Jen, the host, was funny, helpful, and created a great space for everyone.  

The ingredients available were plentiful - some I've heard of (non-alcoholic spirits, dried coconut, juices, citrus, etc) and tons which were new to me (beetroot powder, dandelion flowers, honey powder).  I created several mocktails, and really enjoyed experimenting with flavors.  

I will definitely be back

review.name: Really fun!
review.reviewBody:
We just visited the Mad Scientist mocktail lab, and had a great time.   

The space itself is really unique, upstairs in Melrose Market.  The loft is decorated nicely with a mix of science, fun, and old fashioned library style.  There are also tons of ingredients, arranged at multiple stations across the lab/loft.  

Jen, the host, was fun, informative, and easy going.  She gave a tour, and has clearly put a lot of thought into this experience.  

As I mentioned above, there are TONS of ingredients available, so this is a good space to try new things that you may not have tried before.  

You can choose your own adventure here, and I chose to follow one recipe at first, then create my own concoctions afterwards.  

Highly recommend!

review.name: Mocktail lab galore
review.reviewBody:
This mocktail lab comes with a cold smoker which you can use cherry, hickory, oak and mesquite wood to infuse anything you want.  I chose to infuse dried ginger and papaya with pecan wood and dried pineapple with cherry wood.  There's also a whole section of dried powders.  I used kava, li hing mui, coconut cream, pomegranate, guava, lychee and honey powder.  Above the dried powders, there's various teas to infuse in distilled water.  I chose passion fruit flower.  In addition, mocktail booze in rum and tequila form are available as well as a range of bitters.  Jen also provides juices from Pressed juicery, pomegranate juice, calpico, lemonade and fresh lime, lemon, ginger and maraschino and luxardo cherries.  We also had various glitters, salt and sugars to play with.

The combinations are endless!

On the snack table, there were corn nuts, red vines, various nuts with a nut cracker, chocolate covered almonds, proscuitto, coppa and Dubliner cheese.  I would recommend eating afterwards since these are small bites.  

There's also a vending machine with fortune cookies with NSFW messages inside.

Overall a great experience and would love to experience it again

name: Herban Adventure
description:
Have you ever been curious about how the legal cannabis industry works? Explore behind the scenes of Seattle’s cannabis industry and culture. This tour takes you down the rabbit hole of America’s fastest growing start-up industry. On this seed-to-sale adventure, you’ll get an exclusive tour of a cannabis garden, a private look into how concentrates are re-shaping the industry, and a visit to one of the finest retailers in the business. Featured partnerships include Craft Elixirs, Heylo Cannabis, Dawg Star, Skyhigh Gardens, Ganja Goddess and The Bakeréé — our featured retailer where you can enjoy a tour discount on partner products!
